stage.name: Stage1
stage.narrative: 始This Internal Business Object provides the ability for processes to interact with working days defined in calendars within System Manager.終

stage.name: Get Working Days In Range
stage.narrative: 始Gets the working days as configured on the specified calendar, starting and ending on the specified dates.終

input.name: Calendar Name
input.narrative: The name of the calendar defined in System Manager

input.name: First Date
input.narrative: The first date to consider working days from

input.name: Last Date
input.narrative: The last date to consider working days until

output.name: Working Days
output.narrative: The working days which fall between the specified dates (inclusive)

input.name: Calendar Name
input.narrative: The name of the calendar defined in System Manager

input.name: First Date
input.narrative: The first date to consider working days from

input.name: Last Date
input.narrative: The last date to consider working days until

output.name: Working Days
output.narrative: The working days which fall between the specified dates (inclusive)

stage.name: Count Working Days In Range

input.name: Calendar Name
input.narrative: The name of the calendar defined in System Manager

input.name: First Date

input.name: Last Date
input.narrative: The last date to consider working days until

output.name: Days
output.narrative: The number of working days found within the specified range, inclusive

input.name: Calendar Name

input.name: First Date

input.name: Last Date

output.name: Days

stage.name: Is Working Day
stage.narrative: 始Checks if the given date is a working day or not according to the specified calendar.終

input.name: Calendar Name
input.narrative: The name of the calendar defined in System Manager

input.name: Date
input.narrative: The date to consider whether it is a working day or not

output.name: Is Working Day
output.narrative: True to indicate the given date was a working day, False otherwise

input.name: Calendar Name
input.narrative: The name of the calendar defined in System Manager

input.name: Date
input.narrative: The date to consider whether it is a working day or not

output.name: Is Working Day
output.narrative: True to indicate the given date was a working day, False otherwise

stage.name: Add Working Days
stage.narrative: 始Adds the specified number of working days to a start date returning the result. In order to get the next working day after a known date, use a 'Days' value of 1. To get the previous working day, use a value of -1. Note that calling this action with a Days value of 0 will always return Start Date, regardless of whether that is a working day or not.終

input.name: Calendar Name
input.narrative: The name of the calendar defined in System Manager

input.name: Date
input.narrative: The date to which the number of working days should be added

input.name: Days
input.narrative: The number of days to be added. Note that a value of zero will always return Start Date, even if it is not a working day

output.name: Result Date
output.narrative: The date with the specified number of days added to it

input.name: Calendar Name
input.narrative: The name of the calendar defined in System Manager

input.name: Date
input.narrative: The date to which the number of working days should be added

input.name: Days
input.narrative: The number of days to be added. Note that a value of zero will always return Start Date, even if it is not a working day

output.name: Result Date
output.narrative: The date with the specified number of days added to it

stage.name: Is Weekend
stage.narrative: 始Checks if the given date falls outside the working week - ie. the weekend - as defined in the specified calendar終

input.name: Calendar Name
input.narrative: The name of the calendar defined in System Manager

input.name: Date
input.narrative: The date to check

output.name: Is Weekend
output.narrative: True to indicate that the given date falls outside the working week defined in the calendar; False otherwise.

input.name: Calendar Name
input.narrative: The name of the calendar defined in System Manager

input.name: Date
input.narrative: The date to check

output.name: Is Weekend
output.narrative: True to indicate that the given date falls outside the working week defined in the calendar; False otherwise.

stage.name: Is Public Holiday
stage.narrative: 始Checks if the given date represents an enabled public holiday as defined in the specified calendar. Note that if a public holiday is configured to be ignored in a calendar, this action will return False for that date終

input.name: Calendar Name
input.narrative: The name of the calendar defined in System Manager

input.name: Date
input.narrative: The date to check

output.name: Is Public Holiday
output.narrative: True to indicate that the given date falls on a public holiday; False otherwise

output.name: Name
output.narrative: If date is a public holiday, this contains the label of that public holiday, otherwise blank

input.name: Calendar Name
input.narrative: The name of the calendar defined in System Manager

input.name: Date
input.narrative: The date to check

output.name: Is Public Holiday
output.narrative: True to indicate that the given date falls on a public holiday; False otherwise

output.name: Name
output.narrative: If date is a public holiday, this contains the label of that public holiday, otherwise blank

stage.name: Get Public Holidays In Range

input.name: Calendar Name
input.narrative: The name of the calendar defined in System Manager

input.name: First Date

input.name: Last Date
input.narrative: The last date to consider public holidays until

output.name: Public Holidays
output.narrative: The public holidays which fall between the specified dates (inclusive)
